        <div>
            <a href="../../index.html" class="text-slate-400 hover:text-amber-600 transition-colors font-bold uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest flex items-center gap-2">
                <i data-lucide="arrow-left" size="14"></i> Back to Dashboard
            </a>
        </div>
        <button onclick="window.print()" class="bg-amber-600 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded-full font-bold shadow-lg hover:bg-amber-700 transition-all flex items-center gap-2">
            <i data-lucide="printer" size="16"></i> Print to PDF
        </button>
    </nav>
    
    <article class="page">
        <header class="mb-12 border-b-2 border-amber-50 pb-8">
            <p class="font-sans font-bold text-amber-600 uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest mb-2 italic">Music // The Tone Bars</p>
            <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 leading-tight">Sensorial Introduction to the Tone Bars</h1>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400 italic">Guide: Elim Lee // April 1st Sprint // AMI Elementary</p>
        </header>

        <section class="material-box">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-bold text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-2">Material Overview</h3>
            <div class="text-sm text-slate-700 italic space-y-3">
                <p><strong>Construction:</strong> The tone bars are evenly wide blocks, painted black and white to mimic the piano keyboard. Unlike a piano, the black keys are not indented; they sit flush in the layout.</p>
                <p><strong>The Playing Mechanism:</strong> To play a note, use two fingers to tug the intended tone bar forward by its plastic casing. Once pulled out, tap the silver center of the bar with the mallet.</p>
                <p><strong>The Pattern Strip:</strong> A "Transposer" made of a slip of poster paper. It features Sharpie-written numbers (1-8) with deliberately blank squares in between to emphasize <strong>Whole Steps</strong>.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="material-box">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-bold text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-2">Purpose</h3>
            <p class="text-sm font-medium italic text-slate-600">To introduce the tone bars as a sensorial tool for pitch refinement and to discover the mathematical pattern of the major scale using the transposer strip.</p>
            <h3 class="font-sans font-bold text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mt-4 mb-2">Materials</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm font-medium italic text-slate-600 list-disc ml-5">
                <li><strong>25 Tone Bars:</strong> Arranged chromatically on two boards.</li>
                <li><strong>Mallet:</strong> With a hard rubber head.</li>
                <li><strong>Major Scale Pattern Strip:</strong> Numbered 1-8 with whole-step gaps.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-amber-600 mb-8 border-b pb-2 italic">Part I: Matching and Grading</h2>

            <div class="action">Invite the children to the rug. Set out two sets of white tone bars in random order.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"You have worked with the bells to find twin sounds. The tone bars work the same way. We are going to find the sounds that match exactly."</div>

            <div class="action">Strike a control bar, then search for its match in the second set.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"These two sounds are twins. They belong together."</div>

            <div class="action">Invite the child to arrange one set from the deepest pitch to the highest.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"Now we have a staircase of sound, climbing from low to high."</div>

            <div class="illustrate">
                <svg width="400" height="150" viewBox="0 0 400 150" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <!-- Uniform Bases (Plastic) -->
                    <rect x="50" y="30" width="30" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8" rx="2"/>
                    <rect x="90" y="30" width="30" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8" rx="2"/>
                    <rect x="130" y="30" width="30" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8" rx="2"/>
                    <rect x="170" y="30" width="30" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8" rx="2"/>
                    <rect x="210" y="30" width="30" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8" rx="2"/>
                    
                    <!-- Silver Metal Bars (Getting shorter for higher pitch) -->
                    <rect x="55" y="35" width="20" height="70" fill="#CBD5E1" stroke="#64748B"/>
                    <circle cx="65" cy="40" r="1.5" fill="#475569"/> <circle cx="65" cy="100" r="1.5" fill="#475569"/> <!-- pegs -->
                    
                    <rect x="95" y="40" width="20" height="60" fill="#CBD5E1" stroke="#64748B"/>
                    <circle cx="105" cy="45" r="1.5" fill="#475569"/> <circle cx="105" cy="95" r="1.5" fill="#475569"/>
                    
                    <rect x="135" y="45" width="20" height="50" fill="#CBD5E1" stroke="#64748B"/>
                    <circle cx="145" cy="50" r="1.5" fill="#475569"/> <circle cx="145" cy="90" r="1.5" fill="#475569"/>
                    
                    <rect x="175" y="50" width="20" height="40" fill="#CBD5E1" stroke="#64748B"/>
                    <circle cx="185" cy="55" r="1.5" fill="#475569"/> <circle cx="185" cy="85" r="1.5" fill="#475569"/>
                    
                    <rect x="215" y="55" width="20" height="30" fill="#CBD5E1" stroke="#64748B"/>
                    <circle cx="225" cy="60" r="1.5" fill="#475569"/> <circle cx="225" cy="80" r="1.5" fill="#475569"/>

                    <!-- Directional Arrow -->
                    <path d="M50 130 L230 130" stroke="#1E293B" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>
                    <defs><marker id="arrowhead" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="7" refX="0" refY="3.5" orient="auto"><polygon points="0 0, 10 3.5, 0 7" fill="#1E293B" /></marker></defs>
                    <text x="85" y="145" font-family="Inter" font-size="8" fill="#64748B">GRADING LOW TO HIGH (Shorter metal = Higher Pitch)</text>
                </svg>
                <div class="illustrate-label">Fig 1.1: Grading by pitch (Note the uniform plastic bases)</div>
            </div>

            <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-amber-600 mt-16 mb-8 border-b pb-2 italic">Part II: The Major Scale & The Transposer</h2>

            <div class="aside-box text-sm italic text-amber-900 leading-relaxed mb-8">
                "Guide Tip: When striking the bars, remember the principle: <strong>'Never Louder Than Lovely.'</strong> Strike with a top-down motion and allow the mallet to bounce back immediately to let the silver center vibrate freely."
            </div>

            <div class="action">Place the bars in keyboard order. Slide the pattern strip underneath the bars.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"Every major scale follows a secret code. We use this numbered strip to find the notes for any scale, starting anywhere we like."</div>

            <div class="action">Place the strip starting on 'C'. Use two fingers to tug the bars numbered 1 through 8 forward.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"Watch as I pull out the bars the pattern has chosen for us. Now we play only these."</div>

            <div class="illustrate">
                <svg width="450" height="180" viewBox="0 0 450 180" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <!-- Base board background -->
                    <rect x="45" y="15" width="335" height="110" fill="#F8FAFC" stroke="#E2E8F0"/>
                    
                    <!-- Tone Bars (W, B, W, B, W, W, B, W, B, W, B, W, W) -->
                    <!-- C -->  <rect x="50" y="40" width="25" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8"/><rect x="55" y="45" width="15" height="70" fill="#CBD5E1"/><circle cx="62.5" cy="80" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- C# --> <rect x="75" y="20" width="25" height="80" fill="#1E293B" stroke="#0F172A"/><rect x="80" y="25" width="15" height="70" fill="#94A3B8"/><circle cx="87.5" cy="60" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- D -->  <rect x="100" y="40" width="25" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8"/><rect x="105" y="45" width="15" height="70" fill="#CBD5E1"/><circle cx="112.5" cy="80" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- D# --> <rect x="125" y="20" width="25" height="80" fill="#1E293B" stroke="#0F172A"/><rect x="130" y="25" width="15" height="70" fill="#94A3B8"/><circle cx="137.5" cy="60" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- E -->  <rect x="150" y="40" width="25" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8"/><rect x="155" y="45" width="15" height="70" fill="#CBD5E1"/><circle cx="162.5" cy="80" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- F -->  <rect x="175" y="40" width="25" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8"/><rect x="180" y="45" width="15" height="70" fill="#CBD5E1"/><circle cx="187.5" cy="80" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- F# --> <rect x="200" y="20" width="25" height="80" fill="#1E293B" stroke="#0F172A"/><rect x="205" y="25" width="15" height="70" fill="#94A3B8"/><circle cx="212.5" cy="60" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- G -->  <rect x="225" y="40" width="25" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8"/><rect x="230" y="45" width="15" height="70" fill="#CBD5E1"/><circle cx="237.5" cy="80" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- G# --> <rect x="250" y="20" width="25" height="80" fill="#1E293B" stroke="#0F172A"/><rect x="255" y="25" width="15" height="70" fill="#94A3B8"/><circle cx="262.5" cy="60" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- A -->  <rect x="275" y="40" width="25" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8"/><rect x="280" y="45" width="15" height="70" fill="#CBD5E1"/><circle cx="287.5" cy="80" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- A# --> <rect x="300" y="20" width="25" height="80" fill="#1E293B" stroke="#0F172A"/><rect x="305" y="25" width="15" height="70" fill="#94A3B8"/><circle cx="312.5" cy="60" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- B -->  <rect x="325" y="40" width="25" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8"/><rect x="330" y="45" width="15" height="70" fill="#CBD5E1"/><circle cx="337.5" cy="80" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>
                    <!-- C -->  <rect x="350" y="40" width="25" height="80" fill="#FFF" stroke="#94A3B8"/><rect x="355" y="45" width="15" height="70" fill="#CBD5E1"/><circle cx="362.5" cy="80" r="3" fill="#FFF"/>

                    <!-- The Transposer Strip -->
                    <rect x="50" y="130" width="325" height="25" fill="#FEF08A" stroke="#CA8A04"/>
                    
                    <!-- Grid Lines on Strip -->
                    <line x1="75" y1="130" x2="75" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <line x1="100" y1="130" x2="100" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <line x1="125" y1="130" x2="125" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <line x1="150" y1="130" x2="150" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <line x1="175" y1="130" x2="175" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <line x1="200" y1="130" x2="200" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <line x1="225" y1="130" x2="225" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <line x1="250" y1="130" x2="250" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <line x1="275" y1="130" x2="275" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <line x1="300" y1="130" x2="300" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <line x1="325" y1="130" x2="325" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>
                    <line x1="350" y1="130" x2="350" y2="155" stroke="#CA8A04" stroke-width="1"/>

                    <!-- Numbers & Blanks -->
                    <text x="59" y="147" font-family="Inter" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#854D0E">1</text>
                    <!-- Blank -->
                    <text x="109" y="147" font-family="Inter" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#854D0E">2</text>
                    <!-- Blank -->
                    <text x="159" y="147" font-family="Inter" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#854D0E">3</text>
                    <text x="184" y="147" font-family="Inter" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#854D0E">4</text>
                    <!-- Blank -->
                    <text x="234" y="147" font-family="Inter" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#854D0E">5</text>
                    <!-- Blank -->
                    <text x="284" y="147" font-family="Inter" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#854D0E">6</text>
                    <!-- Blank -->
                    <text x="334" y="147" font-family="Inter" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#854D0E">7</text>
                    <text x="359" y="147" font-family="Inter" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#854D0E">8</text>

                </svg>
                <div class="illustrate-label">Fig 1.2: Transposer strip aligned to C Major. Note the continuous, non-indented row of tone bars.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="action">Strike the silver center of the pulled-out bars in sequence.</div>
            <div class="dialogue">"When we start on C, the pattern lands only on white bars. But if we move the strip to start on G, the pattern will tell us to use a black bar. The pattern is the law."</div>

            <div class="aside-box text-sm italic text-amber-900 leading-relaxed">
                "The strip acts as a bridge between the physical distance of the bars and the mathematical logic of the scale. Ensure the child uses a steady pincer grip on the mallet to produce a clear, sustained ring."
            </div>
        </section>

        <footer class="mt-20 pt-8 border-t text-[10px] font-sans text-slate-300 uppercase tracking-widest text-center">
            Elim Lee // Semester 4 Sprint // AMI Elementary
        </footer>
    </article>
